The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 October is 81,036 (9,339.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 07 October, there were 2,395 new confirmed cases (276.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 September, there were 2,566 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 7% (171 fewer cases).
